    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>Philomena Falls served with the Women's Army Auxiliary Corps during World War II.  After the war, she returned to Germany where she was a teacher in the Army of Occupation school system. She also taught in Japan in 1954-1955, then returned to Michigan to teach in public schools, later becoming a principal.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The collection consists of correspondence, scrapbooks, and photograph albums.  The collection is of primary value for its documentation, both printed and visual, of Philomena Falls service with the Women's Army Auxiliary Corps and for her extended stays in Germany and Japan as a teacher.</p>
    </scopecontent>
